  "claim_paragraph": "Using experimental TP53 crystal structures as an external geometric ground truth, Block 10B repairs WT reference selection before making any mechanistic claim. The repaired broad subset contains 26 WT-vs-mutant entry pairs covering 11 unique TP53 missense variants, and the strict state-matched subset keeps 24 entry pairs across 11 variants. The primary analysis runs on `strict_variant_level` using `excess local RMSD` as the structural target. Within the predeclared covariance family (`frob_dist`, `trace_ratio`, `sps_log`), the strongest metric is `sps_log` with Spearman -0.527 (absolute 0.527) against `excess_local_rmsd_median`, while scalar likelihood reaches Spearman 0.455 (absolute 0.455), for an absolute covariance-minus-likelihood gap of 0.073. This still needs to be described with care, but it directly addresses the reviewer question of whether covariance is merely a nonlinear rewrite of likelihood: after repairing structural controls, the covariance side remains more tightly coupled to structural tension than the scalar sequence-surprise score."
